    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "the \"lack of debris\" thing is exactly what i'm talking about. like, the descent engine should have kicked up a massive amount of dust but the photos look too \"clean,\" almost like they were composited or staged to hide what was actually in the background. and i noticed a lot of the high-res scans from that period have weird digital artifacts or \"noise\" in the sectors where the shadows are darkest. do you think it's possible the government used those technical \"glitches\" to mask the presence of a structure or something non-natural on the lunar surface?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
